Sample Transportation

agents:
	humans: Nurse
	robots: LabRobot, SampleTransporter
locations: PatientF, Lab
resources: Sample

PatientF:
	robots: SampleTransporter
	SampleTransporter: default moveTo PatientF: checkSamples
	         1: moveTo PatientF
	     2: flag sample1
	     3: skip if !sample_ready(sample1)
	        sample_transportRequest(sample1)

Nurse:
	SampleTransporter: 
	4: moveTo Lab if sample1_valid(sample1)
	  else: stop

Lab:
	1: default moveTo Lab
	 LabRobot: default pickSample
 paramIntarameter skip if !LabRobot
	   pick sample1 if time<transportProtocols(sample1)
	 2: loadSample(sample1)
	 3: recordlog(sample1, pickup_location="Lab",
                   pickup_time="time")
	 4: skip if !addBarcodeInformation
	        barcodeScanner
	 5: loadInfoFromScanner(sample1)
	 6: dataSetProcess(sample1)
	 7: updateTransportStatistics(sample1)

Model Validation:
-Scoping: Each agent used is declared in the header.
-SubSequence Ordering:  The line numbers start at 1 and increase in each section of the model. No gaps in numbering.
-Recursive Action Assignment: Each robot only has one assigned sequence, none overlap.
-Verb Semantic Mapping: The actions fetch and deliver used were identified and relating to texto are related to picked and loadSample but still semantic are the closest unused for final functionality
